PBG SA, Netia, Cyfrowy Polsat: Central Europe Equity Preview

-- B y   K a t y a   A n d r u s z
-- 
2011-04-26T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/pbg-sa-netia-cyfrowy-polsat-central-europe-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in central
European markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names. Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index fell 0.6 percent on April 21, while
the Czech PX Index declined 0.3 percent on April 22 and
Hungary’s BUX Index fell 0.5 percent on April 22. All three
markets were closed on April 25 for a public holiday.  Cyfrowy Polsat SA (CPS)  : Poland’s biggest satellite
television broadcaster completed the purchase of Telewizja
Polsat SA, controlled by billionaire Zygmunt Solorz-Zak, for
3.75 billion zloty ($1.4 billion). The new entity will become
Poland’s biggest media company, Cyfrowy Polsat said in an e-
mailed statement on April 21. Shares declined 0.3 percent to
16.18 zloty.  Netia SA (NET)  : Poland’s second-largest fixed-line phone
company, is one of four companies that placed initial bids for
Dialog SA, the operator that KGHM Polska Miedz SA is seeking to
sell for at least 825 million zloty, Parkiet newspaper reported
on April 22. Shares rose 0.4 percent to 5.3 zloty.  PBG SA (PBG)  : Poland’s second-largest builder by market value
sees no “fundamental” basis behind the recent decline of its
share price on the  Warsaw Stock Exchange , Chief Financial
Officer Przemyslaw Szkudlarczyk said in a letter to shareholders
published on the company’s website on April 22. PBG’s forecast
of reaching net income of 200 million zloty on sales of 2.3
billion zloty this year is “cautious,” he said. The shares
fell 2.5 percent to 159.9 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katya Andrusz in Warsaw at 
 kandrusz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
